obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32376)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st August, 1963, vide notification No. S.O. 1925, dated 8th July, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32376&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Marine Insurance Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32377)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32377&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "contract of marine insurance" means a contract of marine insurance as defined by section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "freight" includes the profit derivable by a ship-owner from the employment of his ship to`
  line `carry his own goods or other movables, as well as freight payable by a third party, but does not`
  line `include passage money;`
  line
  line `(c) "insurable property" means any ship, goods or other movables which are exposed to maritime`
  line perils;
  line
  line `(d) "marine adventure" includes any adventure where--`
  line
  line `(i) any insurable property is exposed to maritime perils;`
  line
  line `(ii) the earnings or acquisition of any freight, passage money, commission, profit or other`
  line `pecuniary benefit, or the security for any advances, loans, or disbursements is endangered by the`
  line `exposure of insurable property to maritime perils;`
  line
  line `(iii) any liability to a third party may be incurred by the owner of, or other person interested`
  line `in or responsible for, insurable property by reason of maritime perils;`
  line
  line `(e) "maritime perils" means the perils consequent on, or incidental to, the navigation of the sea,`
  line `that is to say, perils of the seas, fire, war perils, pirates, rovers, thieves, captures, seizures, restraints`
  line `and detainments of princes and peoples, jettisons, barratry and any other perils which are either of the`
  line `like kind or may be designated by the policy;`
  line
  line `(f) "movables" means any movable tangible property, other than the ship, and includes money,`
  line `valuable securities and other documents;`
  line
  line `(g) "policy" means a marine policy;`
  line
  line `(h) "ship" includes every description of vessel used in navigation;`
  line
  line `(i) "suit" includes counter-claim and set-off.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32378)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Marine insurance defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32378&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A contract of marine insurance is an agreement whereby the insurer`
  line `undertakes to indemnify the assured, in the manner and to the extent thereby agreed, against marine`
  line `losses, that is to say, the losses incidental to marine adventure.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32379)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Mixed sea and land risks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32379&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A contract of marine insurance may, by its express terms, or by`
  line `usage of trade, be extended so as to protect the assured against losses on inland waters or on any land risk`
  line `which may be incidental to any sea voyage.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a ship in course of building or the launch of a ship, or any adventure analogous to a marine`
  line `adventure, is covered by a policy in the form of a marine policy, the provisions of this Act, in so far as`
  line `applicable, shall apply thereto, but except as by this section provided, nothing in this Act shall alter or affect any rule of law applicable to any contract of insurance other than a contract of marine insurance as`
  line `by this Act defined.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"An adventure analogous to a marine adventure" includes an adventure where any`
  line `ship, goods or other movables are exposed to perils incidental to local or inland transit.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32380)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Lawful marine adventure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32380&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, every lawful marine adventure`
  line `may be the subject of a contract of marine insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32381)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Avoidance of wagering contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32381&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every contract of marine insurance by way of wagering is`
  line void.
  line
  line `(2) A contract of marine insurance is deemed to be a wagering contract:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the assured has not an insurable interest as defined by this Act, and the contract is`
  line `entered into with no expectation of acquiring such an interest; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the policy is made "interest or no interest", or "without further proof of interest than the`
  line `policy itself, or "without benefit of salvage to the insurer", or subject to any other like term:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where there is no possibility of salvage, a policy may be effected without benefit of`
  line `salvage to the insurer.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32382)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Insurable interest defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32382&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, every person has an`
  line `insurable interest who is interested in a marine adventure.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular a person is interested in a marine adventure where he stands in any legal or equitable`
  line `relation to the adventure or to any insurable property at risk therein, in consequence of which he may`
  line `benefit by the safety or due arrival of insurable property, or may be prejudiced by its loss, or by damage`
  line `thereto, or by the detention thereof, or may incur liability in respect thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32383)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `When interest must attach.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32383&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assured must be interested in the subject-matter insured at`
  line `the time of the loss, though he need not be interested when the insurance is effected:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the subject-matter is insured "lost or not lost", the assured may recover although`
  line `he may not have acquired his interest until after the loss, unless at the time of effecting the contract of`
  line `insurance the assured was aware of the loss, and the insurer was not.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the assured has no interest at the time of the loss, he cannot acquire interest by any act or`
  line `election after he is aware of the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32384)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Defeasible or contingent interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32384&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) A defeasible interest is insurable, as also is a contingent`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, where the buyer of goods has insured them, he has an insurable interest,`
  line `notwithstanding that he might, at his election, have rejected the goods, or have treated them as at the`
  line `sellers risk, by reason of the latter's delay in making delivery or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32385)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Partial interest.`
  content `A partial interest of any nature is insurable.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32385&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32386)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Reinsurance.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32386&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The insurer under a contract of marine insurance has an insurable interest in`
  line `his risk, and may reinsure in respect of it.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the policy otherwise provides, the original assured has no right or interest in respect of`
  line `such reinsurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32387)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Bottomry.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32387&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The lender of money on bottomry or respondentia has an insurable interest in respect`
  line `of the loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32388)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Master’s and seamen’s wages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32388&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The master or any member of the crew of a ship has an`
  line `insurable interest in respect of his wages.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32389)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Advance freight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32389&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `In the case of advance freight, the person advancing the freight has an`
  line `insurable interest, in so far as such freight is not repayable in case of loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32390)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Charges of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32390&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The assured has an insurable interest in the charges of any insurance`
  line `which he may effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32391)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Quantum of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32391&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the subject-matter insured is mortgaged, the mortgagor has an`
  line `insurable interest in the full value thereof, and the mortgagee has an insurable interest in respect of any`
  line `sum due or to become due under the mortgage.`
  line
  line `(2) A mortgagee, consignee, or other person having an interest in the subject-matter insured may`
  line `insure on behalf and for the benefit of other persons interested as well as for his own benefit.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner of insurable property has an insurable interest in respect of the full value thereof,`
  line `notwithstanding that some third person may have agreed, or be liable to indemnify him in case of loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32392)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Assignment of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32392&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where the assured assigns or otherwise parts with his interest in the`
  line `subject-matter insured, he does not thereby transfer to the assignee his rights under the contract of`
  line `insurance, unless there be an express or implied agreement with the assignee to that effect.`
  line
  line `But the provisions of this section do not affect transmission of interest by operation of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32393)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Measure of insurable value.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32393&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any express provision or valuation in the policy, the`
  line `insurable value of the subject-matter insured must be ascertained as follows:--`
  line
  line `(1) In insurance on ship, the insurable value is the value, at the commencement of the risk, of the`
  line `ship, including her outfit, provisions, and stores for the officers and crew, money advanced for`
  line `seamen's wages, and other disbursements (if any) incurred to make the ship fit for the voyage or`
  line `adventure contemplated by the policy, plus the charges of insurance upon the whole.`
  line
  line `The insurable value, in the case of a steamship, includes also the machinery, boilers, and coals`
  line `and engine stores if owned by the assured; in the case of a ship driven by power other than steam`
  line `includes also the machinery and fuels and engine stores, if owned by the assured; and in the case of a`
  line `ship engaged in a special trade, includes also the ordinary fittings requisite for that trade.`
  line
  line `(2) In insurance on freight, whether paid in advance or otherwise, the insurable value is the gross`
  line `amount of the freight at the risk of the assured, plus the charges of insurance.`
  line
  line `(3) In insurance on goods or merchandise, the insurable value is the prime cost of the property`
  line `insured, plus the expenses of and incidental to shipping and the charges of insurance upon the whole.`
  line
  line `(4) In insurance on any other subject-matter, the insurable value is the amount at the risk of the`
  line `assured when the policy attaches, plus the charges of insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32394)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Insurance is uberrimae fidei.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32394&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `A contract of marine insurance is a contract based upon the`
  line `utmost good faith, and if the utmost good faith be not observed by either party, the contract may be`
  line `avoided by the other party.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32395)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Disclosure by assured.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32395&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, the assured must disclose to`
  line `the insurer, before the contract is concluded, every material circumstance which, is known to the assured,`
  line `and the assured is deemed to know every circumstance which, in the ordinary course of business, ought to`
  line `be known to him. If the assured fails to make such disclosure, the insurer may avoid the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) Every circumstance is material which would influence the judgment of a prudent insurer in fixing`
  line `the premium, or determining whether he will take the risk.`
  line
  line `(3) In the absence of inquiry the following circumstances need not be disclosed, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any circumstance which diminishes the risk;`
  line
  line `(b) any circumstance which is known or presumed to be known to the insurer. The insurer is`
  line `presumed to know matters of common notoriety or knowledge, and matters which an insurer in the`
  line `ordinary course of his business as such ought to know;`
  line
  line `(c) any circumstance as to which information is waived by the insurer;`
  line
  line `(d) any circumstance which it is superfluous to disclose by reason of any express or implied`
  line warranty.
  line
  line `(4) Whether any particular circumstance, which is not disclosed, be material or not is, in each case, a`
  line `question of fact.`
  line
  line `(5) The term "circumstance" includes any communication made to, or information received by, the`
  line assured.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32396)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disclosure by agent effecting insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32396&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the preceding section as`
  line `to circumstances which need not be disclosed, where an insurance is effected for the assured by an agent,`
  line `the agent must disclose to the insurer--`
  line
  line `(a) every material circumstance which is known to himself, and an agent to insure is deemed to`
  line `know every circumstance which in the ordinary course of business ought to be known by, or to have`
  line `been communicated to, him; and`
  line
  line `(b) every material circumstance which the assured is bound to disclose, unless it comes to his`
  line `knowledge too late to communicate it to the agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32397)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Representations pending negotiation of contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32397&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every material representation made by`
  line `the assured or his agent to the insurer during the negotiations for the contract, and before the contract is`
  line `concluded, must be true. If it be untrue the insurer may avoid the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) A representation is material which would influence the judgment of a prudent insurer in fixing the`
  line `premium, or determining whether he will take the risk.`
  line
  line `(3) A representation may be either as to a matter of fact, or as to a matter of expectation or belief.`
  line
  line `(4) A representation as to a matter of fact is true, if it be substantially correct, that is to say, if the`
  line `difference between what is represented and what is actually correct would not be considered material by a`
  line `prudent insurer.`
  line
  line `(5) A representation as to a matter of expectation or belief is true if it be made in good faith.`
  line
  line `(6) A representation may be withdrawn or corrected before the contract is concluded.`
  line
  line `(7) Whether a particular representation be material or not, is, in each case, a question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32398)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `When contract is deemed to be concluded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32398&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `A contract of marine insurance is deemed to be`
  line `concluded when the proposal of the assured is accepted by the insurer, whether the policy be then issued`
  line `or not; and for the purpose of showing when the proposal was accepted, reference may be made to the`
  line `slip, covering note or other customary memorandum of the contract, although it be unstamped.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32399)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Contract must be embodied in policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32399&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `A contract of marine insurance shall not be admitted in`
  line `evidence unless it is embodied in a marine policy in accordance with this Act. The policy may be`
  line `executed and issued either at the time when the contract is concluded, or afterwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32400)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `What policy must specify.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32400&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `A marine policy must specify--`
  line
  line `(1) the name of the assured, or of some person who effects the insurance on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(2) the subject-matter insured and the risk insured against;`
  line
  line `(3) the voyage, or period of time, or both, as the case may be, covered by the insurance;`
  line
  line `(4) the sum or sums insured;`
  line
  line `(5) the name or names of the insurer or insurers.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32401)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Signature of insurer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32401&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A marine policy must be signed by or on behalf of the insurer.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a policy is subscribed by or on behalf of two or more insurers, each subscription, unless the`
  line `contrary be expressed, constitutes a distinct contract with the assured.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32402)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Voyage and time policies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32402&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the contract is to insure the subject-matter at and from, or`
  line `from one place to another or others, the policy is called a "voyage policy", and, where the contract is to`
  line `insure the subject-matter for a definite period of time, the policy is called a "time policy". A contract for`
  line `both voyage and time may be included in the same policy.`
  line
  line `(2) A time policy which is made for any time exceeding twelve months is invalid.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32403)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Designation and subject-matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32403&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The subject-matter insured must be designated in a`
  line `marine policy with reasonable certainty.`
  line
  line `(2) The nature and extent of the interest of the assured in the subject-matter insured need not be`
  line `specified in the policy.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the policy designates the subject-matter insured in general terms, it shall be construed to`
  line `apply to the interest intended by the assured to be covered.`
  line
  line `(4) In the application of this section regard shall be had to any usage regulating the designation of the`
  line `subject-matter insured.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32404)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Valued policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32404&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A policy may be either valued or unvalued.`
  line
  line `(2) A valued policy is a policy which specifies the agreed value of the subject-matter insured.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of this Act, and in the absence of fraud, the value fixed by the policy is,`
  line `as between the insurer and assured, conclusive of the insurable value of the subject intended to be insured,`
  line `whether the loss be total or partial.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless the policy otherwise provides, the value fixed by the policy is not conclusive for the`
  line `purpose of determining whether there has been a constructive total loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32405)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Unvalued policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32405&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `An unvalued policy is a policy which does not specify the value of the`
  line `subject-matter insured, but subject to the limit of the sum insured, leaves the insurable value to be`
  line `subsequently ascertained, in the manner hereinbefore explained.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32406)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Floating policy by ship or ships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32406&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A floating policy is a policy which describes the insurance`
  line `in general terms, and leaves the name or names of the ship or ships and other particulars to be defined by`
  line `subsequent declaration.`
  line
  line `(2) The subsequent declaration or declarations may be made by endorsement on the policy, or in other`
  line `customary manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the policy otherwise provides, the declarations must be made in the order of dispatch or`
  line `shipment. They must, in the case of goods, comprise all consignments within the terms of the policy, and`
  line `the value of the goods or other property must be honestly stated, but an omission or erroneous declaration`
  line `may be rectified even after loss or arrival, provided the omission or declaration was made in good faith.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless the policy otherwise provides, where a declaration of value is not made until after notice of`
  line `loss or arrival, the policy must be treated as an unvalued policy as regards the subject-matter of that`
  line declaration.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32407)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Construction of terms in policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32407&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A policy may be in the form in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, and unless the context of the policy otherwise requires, the`
  line `terms and expressions mentioned in the Schedule shall be construed as having the scope and meaning`
  line `assigned to them in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32408)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Premium to be arranged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32408&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an insurance is effected at a premium to be arranged, and`
  line `no arrangement is made, a reasonable premium is payable.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an insurance is effected on the terms that an additional premium is to be arranged in a`
  line `given event, and that event happens but no arrangement is made, then a reasonable additional premium is`
  line payable.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32409)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Double insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32409&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where two or more policies are effected by or on behalf of the assured`
  line `on the same adventure and interest or any part thereof, and the sums insured exceed the indemnity`
  line `allowed by this Act, the assured is said to be over-insured by double insurance.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the assured is over-insured by double insurance--`
  line
  line `(a) the assured, unless the policy otherwise provides, may claim payment from the insurers in`
  line `such order as he may think fit, provided that he is not entitled to receive any sum in excess of the`
  line `indemnity allowed by this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where the policy under which the assured claims is a valued policy, the assured must give`
  line `credit as against the valuation, for any sum received by him under any other policy, without regard to`
  line `the actual value of the subject-matter insured;`
  line
  line `(c) where the policy under which the assured claims is an unvalued policy he must give credit, as`
  line `against the full insurable value, for any sum received by him under any other policy;`
  line
  line `(d) where the assured receives any sum in excess of the indemnity allowed by this Act, he is`
  line `deemed to hold such sum in trust for the insurers, according to their right of contribution among`
  line themselves.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32410)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Nature of warranty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32410&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) A warranty, in the following sections relating to warranties, means a`
  line `promissory warranty, that is to say a warranty by which the assured undertakes that some particular thing`
  line `shall or shall not be done, or that some condition shall be fulfilled, or whereby he affirms or negatives the`
  line `existence of a particular state of facts.`
  line
  line `(2) A warranty may be express or implied.`
  line
  line `(3) A warranty, as above defined, is a condition which must be exactly complied with, whether it be`
  line `material to the risk or not. If it be not so complied with, then, subject to any express provision in the`
  line `policy, the insurer is discharged from liability as from the date of the breach of warranty, but without`
  line `prejudice to any liability incurred by him before that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32411)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `When breach of warranty excused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32411&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Non-compliance with a warranty is excused when, by`
  line `reason of a change of circumstances, the warranty ceases to be applicable to the circumstances of the`
  line `contract, or when compliance with the warranty is rendered unlawful by any subsequent law.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a warranty is broken, the assured cannot avail himself of the defence that the breach has`
  line `been remedied, and the warranty complied with before loss.`
  line
  line `(3) A breach of warranty may be waived by the insurer.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32412)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Express warranties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32412&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) An express warranty may be in any form of words from which the`
  line `intention to warrant is to be inferred.`
  line
  line `(2) An express warranty must be included in, or written upon, the policy, or must be contained in`
  line `some document incorporated by reference into the policy.`
  line
  line `(3) An express warranty does not exclude implied warranty, unless it be inconsistent therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32413)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Warranty of neutrality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32413&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where insurable property, whether ship or goods, is expressly`
  line `warranted neutral, there is an implied condition that the property shall have a neutral character at the`
  line `commencement of the risk, and that, so far as the assured can control the matter, its neutral character shall`
  line `be preserved during the risk.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a ship is expressly warranted "neutral", there is also an implied condition that, so far as the`
  line `assured can control the matter, she shall be properly documented, that is to say, that she shall carry the`
  line `necessary papers to establish her neutrality, and that she shall not falsify or suppress her papers, or use`
  line `simulated papers. If any loss occurs through breach of this condition, the insurer may avoid the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32414)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `No implied warranty of nationality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32414&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `There is no implied warranty as to the nationality of a`
  line `ship, or that her nationality shall not be changed during the risk.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32415)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Warranty of good safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32415&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where the subject-matter insured is warranted "well" or "in good`
  line `safety" on a particular day, it is sufficient if it be safe at any time during that day.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32416)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Warranty of seaworthiness of ship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32416&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) In a voyage policy there is an implied warranty that at`
  line `the commencement of the voyage the ship shall be seaworthy for the purpose of the particular adventure`
  line insured.
  line
  line `(2) Where the policy attaches while the ship is in port, there is also an implied warranty that she shall,`
  line `at the commencement of the risk, be reasonably fit to encounter the ordinary perils of the port.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the policy relates to a voyage which is performed in different stages, during which the ship`
  line `requires different kinds of or further preparation or equipment, there is an implied warranty that at the`
  line `commencement of each stage the ship is seaworthy in respect of such preparation or equipment for the`
  line `purposes of that stage.`
  line
  line `(4) A ship is deemed to be seaworthy when she is reasonably fit in all respects to encounter the`
  line `ordinary perils of the seas of the adventure insured.`
  line
  line `(5) In a time policy there is no implied warranty that the ship shall be seaworthy at any stage of the`
  line `adventure, but where, with the privity of the assured, the ship is sent to sea in an unseaworthy state, the`
  line `insurer is not liable for any loss attributable to unseaworthiness.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (32417)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `No implied warranty that goods are seaworthy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32417&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) In a policy on goods or other moveable`
  line `there is no implied warranty that the goods or movables are seaworthy.`
  line
  line `(2) In a voyage policy on goods or other movables there is an implied warranty that at the`
  line `commencement of the voyage the ship is not only seaworthy as a ship, but also that she is reasonably fit`
  line `to carry the goods or other movables to the destination contemplated by the policy.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (32418)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Warranty of legality.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32418&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `There is an implied warranty that the adventure insured is a lawful one,`
  line `and that, so far as the assured can control the matter, the adventure shall be carried out in a lawful`
  line manner.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (32419)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Implied condition as to commencement of risk.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32419&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the subject-matter is insured by a`
  line `voyage policy "at and from" or "from" a particular place, it is not necessary that the ship should be at that`
  line `place when the contract is concluded, but there is an implied condition that the adventure shall be`
  line `commenced within a reasonable time, and that if the adventure be not so commenced the insurer may`
  line `avoid the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) The implied condition may be negatived by showing that the delay was caused by circumstances`
  line `known to the insurer before the contract was concluded, or by showing that he waived the condition.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (32420)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Alteration of port of departure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32420&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where the place of departure is specified by the policy, and`
  line `the ship instead of sailing from that place sails from any other place, the risk does not attach.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (32421)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Sailing for different destination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32421&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Where the destination is specified in the policy, and the ship,`
  line `instead of sailing for that destination, sails for any other destination, the risk does not attach.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (32422)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Change of voyage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32422&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, after the commencement of the risk, the destination of the ship is`
  line `voluntarily changed from the destination contemplated by the policy, there is said to be a change of`
  line voyage.
  line
  line `(2) Unless the policy otherwise provides, where there is a change of voyage, the insurer is discharged`
  line `from liability as from the time of change, that is to say, as from the time when the determination to`
  line `change it is manifested; and it is immaterial that the ship may not in fact have left the course of voyage`
  line `contemplated by the policy when the loss occurs.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (32423)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title Deviation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32423&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a ship, without lawful excused, deviates from the voyage contemplated by`
  line `the policy, the insured is discharged from liability as from the time of deviation, and it is immaterial that`
  line `the ship may have regained her route before any loss occurs.`
  line
  line `(2) There is a deviation from the voyage contemplated by the policy--`
  line
  line `(a) where the course of the voyage is specifically designated by the policy, and that course is`
  line `departed from; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the course of the voyage is not specifically designated by the policy, but the usual and`
  line `customary course is departed from.`
  line
  line `(3) The intention to deviate is immaterial; there must be a deviation in fact to discharge the insurer`
  line `from his liability under the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (32424)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Several ports of discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32424&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where several ports of discharge are specified by the policy,`
  line `the ship may proceed to all or any of them, but, in the absence of any usage or sufficient cause to the`
  line `contrary, she must proceed to them, or such of them as she goes to, in the order designated by the policy.`
  line `If she does not, there is a deviation.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the policy is to "ports of discharge", within a given area, which are not named, the ship`
  line `must, in the absence of any usage or sufficient cause to the contrary, proceed to them, or such of them as`
  line `she goes to, in their geographical order. If she does not, there is a deviation.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (32425)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Delay in voyage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32425&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a voyage policy, the adventure insured must be prosecuted`
  line `throughout its course with reasonable dispatch, and, if without lawful excuse it is not so prosecuted, the`
  line `insurer is discharged from liability as from the time when the delay became unreasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (32426)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Excuse for deviation or delay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32426&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Deviation or delay in prosecuting the voyage contemplated`
  line `by the policy is excused--`
  line
  line `(a) where authorised by any special term in the policy; or`
  line
  line `(b) where caused by circumstances beyond the control of the master and his employer; or`
  line
  line `(c) where reasonably necessary in order to comply with an express or implied warranty; or`
  line
  line `(d) where reasonably necessary for the safety of the ship or subject-matter insured; or`
  line
  line `(e) for the purpose of saving human life or aiding a ship in distress where human life may be in`
  line `danger; or`
  line
  line `(f) where reasonably necessary for the purpose of obtaining medical or surgical aid for any person`
  line `on board the ship; or`
  line
  line `(g) where caused by the barratrous conduct of the master or crew, if barratry be one of the perils`
  line `insured against.`
  line
  line `(2) When the cause excusing the deviation or delay ceases to operate, the ship must resume her`
  line `course, and prosecute her voyage with reasonable dispatch.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (32427)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `When and how policy is assignable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32427&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) A marine policy may be transferred by assignment`
  line `unless it contains terms expressly prohibiting assignment. It may be assigned either before or after loss.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a marine policy has been assigned so as to pass the beneficial interest in such policy, the`
  line `assignee of the policy is entitled to sue thereon in his own name; and the defendant is entitled to make any`
  line `defence arising out of the contract which he would have been entitled to make if the suit had been brought`
  line `in the name of the person by or on behalf of whom the policy was effected.`
  line
  line `(3) A marine policy may be assigned by endorsement thereon or in other customary manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (32428)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Assured who has no interest cannot assign.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32428&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Where the assured has parted with or lost his`
  line `interest in the subject-matter insured, and has not, before or at the time of so doing expressly or impliedly`
  line `agreed to assign the policy, any subsequent assignment of the policy is inoperative:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section affects the assignment of a policy after loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (32429)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `When premium payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32429&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed, the duty of the assured or his agent to pay`
  line `the premium, and the duty of the insurer to issue the policy to the assured or his agent, are concurrent`
  line `conditions, and the insurer is not bound to issue the policy until payment or tender of the premium.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (32430)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Included and excluded losses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32430&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, and unless the policy`
  line `otherwise provides, the insurer is liable for any loss proximately caused by a peril insured against, but,`
  line `subject as aforesaid, he is not liable for any loss which is not proximately caused by a peril insured`
  line against.
  line
  line `(2) In particular--`
  line
  line `(a) the insurer is not liable for any loss attributable to the wilful misconduct of the assured, but,`
  line `unless the policy otherwise provides, he is liable for any loss proximately caused by a peril insured`
  line `against, even though the loss would not have happened but for the misconduct or negligence of the`
  line `master or crew;`
  line
  line `(b) unless the policy otherwise provides, the insurer on ship or goods is not liable for any loss`
  line `proximately caused by delay, although the delay be caused by a peril insured against;`
  line
  line `(c) unless the policy otherwise provides, the insurer is not liable for ordinary wear and tear,`
  line `ordinary leakage and breakage, inherent vice or nature of the subject-matter insured, or for any loss`
  line `proximately caused by rats or vermin, or for any injury to machinery not proximately caused by`
  line `maritime perils.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (32431)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Partial and total loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32431&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) A loss may be either total or partial. Any loss other than a total loss,`
  line `as hereinafter defined, is a partial loss.`
  line
  line `(2) A total loss may be either an actual total loss, or a constructive total loss.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless a different intention appears from the terms of the policy, an insurance against total loss`
  line `includes a constructive, as well as an actual, total loss.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the assured brings a suit for a total loss and the evidence proves only a partial loss, he may,`
  line `unless the policy otherwise provides, recover for a partial loss.`
  line
  line `(5) Where goods reach their destination in specie, but by reason of obliteration of marks, or`
  line `otherwise, they are incapable of identification, the loss, if any, is partial and not total.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (32432)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Actual total loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32432&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the subject-matter insured is destroyed, or so damaged as to cease`
  line `to be a thing of the kind insured, or where the assured is irretrievably deprived thereof, there is an actual`
  line `total loss.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of an actual total loss no notice of abandonment need be given.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (32433)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Missing ship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32433&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Where the ship concerned in the adventure is missing, and after the lapse of a`
  line `reasonable time no news of her has been received, an actual total loss may be presumed.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (32434)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Effect of transhipment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32434&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where, by a peril insured against, the voyage is interrupted at`
  line `intermediate port or place, under such circumstances as, a part from any special stipulation in the contract`
  line `of a freightment, to justify the master in landing and reshipping the goods or other movables, or in`
  line `transhipping them, and sending them on to their destination, the liability of the insurer continues,`
  line `notwithstanding the landing or transhipment.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (32435)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Constructive total loss defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32435&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any express provision in the policy, there is a`
  line `constructive total loss where the subject-matter insured is reasonably abandoned on account of its actual`
  line `total loss appearing to be unavoidable, or because it could not be preserved from actual total loss without`
  line `an expenditure which would exceed its value when the expenditure had been incurred.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, there is a constructive total loss--`
  line
  line `(i) where the assured is deprived of the possession of his ship or goods by a peril insured`
  line `against, and`
  line
  line `(a) it is unlikely that he can recover the ship or goods, as the case may be, or`
  line
  line `(b) the cost of recovering the ship or goods, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `would exceed their value when recovered; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of damage to a ship, where she is so damaged by a peril insured against that the`
  line `cost of repairing the damage would exceed the value of the ship when repaired.`
  line
  line `In estimating the cost of repairs, no deduction is to be made in respect of general average`
  line `contributions to those repairs payable by other interests, but account is to be taken of the expense of`
  line `future salvage operations and of any future general average contributions to which the ship would be`
  line `liable if required; or`
  line
  line `(iii) In the case of damage to goods, where the cost of repairing the damage and forwarding the`
  line `goods to their destination would exceed their value on arrival.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (32436)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Effect of constructive total loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32436&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a constructive total loss the assured may either`
  line `treat the loss as a partial loss, or abandon the subject-matter insured to the insurer and treat the loss as if it`
  line `were an actual total loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (32437)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Notice of abandonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32437&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, where the assured elects`
  line `to abandon the subject-matter insured to the insurer, he must give notice of abandonment. If he fails to do`
  line `so the loss can only be treated as a partial loss.`
  line
  line `(2) Notice of abandonment may be given in writing, or by word of mouth, or partly in writing and`
  line `partly by word of mouth, and may be given in any terms which indicate the intention of the assured to`
  line `abandon his insured interest in the subject-matter insured unconditionally to the insurer.`
  line
  line `(3) Notice of abandonment must be given with reasonable diligence after the receipt of reliable`
  line `information of the loss, but where the information is of a doubtful character the assured is entitled to a`
  line `reasonable time to make enquiry.`
  line
  line `(4) Where notice of abandonment is properly given, the rights of the assured are not prejudiced by the`
  line `fact that the insurer refuses to accept the abandonment.`
  line
  line `(5) The acceptance of an abandonment may be either express or implied from the conduct of the`
  line `insurer. The mere silence of the insurer after notice is not an acceptance.`
  line
  line `(6) Where notice of abandonment is accepted the abandonment is irrevocable. The acceptance of the`
  line `notice conclusively admits liability for the loss and the sufficiency of the notice.`
  line
  line `(7) Notice of abandonment is unnecessary where at the time when the assured receives information of`
  line `the loss, there would be no possibility of benefit to the insurer if notice were given to him.`
  line
  line `(8) Notice of abandonment may be waived by the insurer.`
  line
  line `(9) When an insurer has reinsured his risk, no notice of abandonment need be given by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (32438)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Effect of abandonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32438&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there is a valid abandonment the insurer is entitled to take`
  line `over the interest of the assured in whatever may remain of the subject-matter insured, and all proprietary`
  line `rights incidental thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the abandonment of a ship, the insurer thereof is entitled to any freight in course of being`
  line `earned, and which is earned by her subsequent to the casualty causing the loss, less the expenses of`
  line `earning it incurred after the casualty; and, where the ship is carrying the owner's goods, the insurer is`
  line `entitled to a reasonable remuneration for the carriage of them subsequent to the casualty causing the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (32439)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Particular average loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32439&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) A particular average loss is a partial loss of the subject-matter`
  line `insured, caused by a peril insured against, and which is not a general average loss.`
  line
  line `(2) Expenses incurred by or on behalf of the assured for the safety or preservation of the`
  line `subject-matter insured, other than general average and salvage charges, are called particular charges.`
  line `Particularly charges are not included in particular average.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (32440)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Salvage charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32440&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any express provision in the policy, salvage charges incurred in`
  line `preventing a loss by perils insured against may be recovered as a loss by those perils.`
  line
  line `(2) "Salvage charges" means the charges recoverable under maritime law by a salvor independently`
  line `of contract. They do not include the expenses of services in the nature of salvage rendered by the assured`
  line `or his agents, or any person employed for hire by them, for the purpose of averting a peril insured against.`
  line `Such expenses, where properly incurred, may be recovered as particular charges or as a general average`
  line `loss, according to the circumstances under which they were incurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (32441)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `General average loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32441&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) A general average loss is a loss caused by or directly consequential`
  line `on a general average act. It includes a general average expenditure as well as a general average sacrifice.`
  line
  line `(2) There is a general average act where any extraordinary sacrifice or expenditure is voluntarily and`
  line `reasonably made or incurred in time of peril for the purpose of preserving the property imperilled in the`
  line `common adventure.`
  line
  line `(3) Where there is a general average loss, the party on whom it falls is entitled, subject to the`
  line `conditions imposed by maritime law, to a rateable contribution from the other parties interested, and such`
  line `contribution is called a general average contribution.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to any express provision in the policy, where the assured has incurred a general average or`
  line `expenditure, he may recover from the insurer in respect of the proportion of the loss which falls upon`
  line `him; and in the case of a general average sacrifice, he may recover from the insurer in respect of the`
  line `whole loss without having enforced his right of contribution from the other parties liable to contribute.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any express provision in the policy, where the assured has paid, or is liable to pay, a`
  line `general average contribution in respect of the interest insured, he may recover therefor from the insurer.`
  line
  line `(6) In the absence of express stipulation, the insurer is not liable for any general average loss or`
  line `contribution where the loss was not incurred for the purpose of avoiding, or in connection with the`
  line `avoidance of a peril insured against.`
  line
  line `(7) Where ship, freight, and cargo, or any two of those interests, are owned by the same assured, the`
  line `liability of the insurer in respect of general average losses or contributions is to be determined as if those`
  line `interests were owned by different persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (32442)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Extent of liability of insurer for loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32442&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sum which the assured can recover in respect of`
  line `a loss on a policy by which he is insured, in the case of an unvalued policy to the full extent of the`
  line `insurable value, or, in the case of a valued policy to the full extent of the value fixed by the policy, is`
  line `called the measure of indemnity.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is a loss recoverable under the policy, the insurer, or each insurer if there be more`
  line `than one, is liable for such proportion of the measure of indemnity as the amount of his subscription bears`
  line `to the value fixed by the policy in the case of a valued policy, or to the insurable value in the case of an`
  line `unvalued policy.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (32443)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Total loss.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32443&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, and to any express provision in the policy,`
  line `where there is a total loss of the subject-matter insured--`
  line
  line `(1) if the policy be a valued policy, the measure of indemnity is the sum fixed by the policy;`
  line
  line `(2) if the policy be an unvalued policy, the measure of indemnity is the insurable value of the`
  line `subject-matter insured.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (32444)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Partial loss of ship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32444&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Where a ship is damaged, but is not totally lost, the measure of indemnity`
  line `subject to any express provision in the policy, is as follows--`
  line
  line `(1) where the ship has been repaired, the assured is entitled to the reasonable cost of the repairs,`
  line `less the customary deductions, but not exceeding the sum insured in respect of any one casualty;`
  line
  line `(2) where the ship has been only partially repaired, the assured is entitled to the reasonable cost of`
  line `such repairs, computed as above, and also to be indemnified for the reasonable depreciation, if any,`
  line `arising from the unrepaired damage, provided that the aggregate amount shall not exceed the cost of`
  line `repairing the whole damage, computed as above;`
  line
  line `(3) where the ship has not been repaired, and has not been sold in her damaged state during the`
  line `risk, the assured is entitled to be indemnified for the reasonable depreciation arising from the`
  line `unrepaired damage, but not exceeding the reasonable cost of repairing such damage, computed as`
  line above;
  line
  line `(4) where the ship has not been repaired, and has been sold in her damaged state during the risk,`
  line `the assured is entitled to be indemnified for the reasonable cost of repairing the damage, computed as`
  line `above, but not exceeding the depreciation in value as ascertained by the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (32445)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Partial loss of freight.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32445&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any express provision in the policy, where there is a partial`
  line `loss of freight, the measure of indemnity is such proportion of the sum fixed by the policy in the case of a`
  line `valued policy or of the insurable value in the case of an unvalued policy, as the proportion of freight lost`
  line `by the assured bears to the whole freight at the risk of the assured under the policy.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (32446)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Partial loss of goods, merchandise, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32446&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a partial loss of goods, merchandise, or`
  line `other movable, the measure of indemnity, subject to any express provision in the policy, is as follows:--`
  line
  line `(1) where part of the goods, merchandise or other movable insured by a valued policy is totally`
  line `lost, the measure of indemnity is such proportion of the sum fixed by the policy as the insurable value`
  line `of the part lost bears to the insurable value of the whole, ascertained as in the case of an unvalued`
  line policy;
  line
  line `(2) where part of the goods, merchandise or other movable insured by an unvalued policy is`
  line `totally lost, the measure of indemnity is the insurable value of the part lost, ascertained as in case of`
  line `total loss;`
  line
  line `(3) where the whole or any part of the goods or merchandise insured has been delivered damaged`
  line `at its destination, the measure of idemnity is such proportion of the sum fixed by the policy in the`
  line `case of a valued policy, or of the insurable value in the case of an unvalued policy, as the difference`
  line `between the gross sound and damaged values at the place of arrival bears to the gross sound value;`
  line
  line `(4) "Gross value" means the wholesale price, or, if there be no such price, the estimated value,`
  line `with, in either case, freight, landing charges, and duty paid beforehand; provided that, in the case of`
  line `goods or merchandise customarily sold in bond, the bonded price is deemed to be the gross value.`
  line `"Gross proceeds" means the actual price obtained at a sale where all charges on sale are paid by the`
  line sellers.
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (32447)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Apportionment of valuation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32447&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where different species of property are insured under a single`
  line `valuation, the valuation must be apportioned over the different species in proportion to their respective`
  line `insurable values, as in the case of an unvalued policy. The insured value of any part of a species is such`
  line `proportion of the total insured value of the same as the insurable value of the part bears to the insurable`
  line `value of the whole, ascertained in both cases as provided by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a valuation has to be apportioned, and particulars of the prime cost of each separate`
  line `species, quality, or description of goods cannot be ascertained, the division of the valuation may be made`
  line `over the net arrived sound values of the different species, qualities, or descriptions of goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (32448)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `General average contributions and salvage charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32448&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any express provision in`
  line `the policy, where the assured has paid, or is liable for, any general average contribution, the measure of`
  line `indemnity is the full amount of such contribution if the subject-matter liable to contribution is insured for`
  line `its full contributory value; but, if such subject-matter be not insured for its full contributory value, or if`
  line `only part of it be insured, the indemnity payable by the insurer must be reduced in proportion to the`
  line `under-insurance, and where there has been a particular average loss which constitutes a deduction from`
  line `the contributory value, and for which the insurer is liable, that amount must be deducted from the insured`
  line `value in order to ascertain what the insurer is liable to contribute.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the insurer is liable for salvage charges the extent of his liabilities must be determined on`
  line `the like principle.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (32449)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Liabilities to third parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32449&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Where the assured has effected an insurance in express terms`
  line `against any liability to a third party, the measure of indemnity, subject to any express provision in the`
  line `policy, is the amount paid or payable by him to such third party in respect of such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (32450)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `General provisions as to measure of indemnity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32450&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there has been a loss in respect of`
  line `any subject-matter not expressly provided for in the foregoing provisions of this Act, the measure of`
  line `indemnity shall be ascertained as nearly as may be, in accordance with those provisions, in so far as`
  line `applicable to the particular case.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in the provisions of this Act relating to the measure of indemnity shall affect the rules`
  line `relating to double insurance, or prohibit the insurer from disproving interest wholly or in part, or from`
  line `showing that at the time of the loss the whole or any part of the subject-matter insured was not at risk`
  line `under the policy.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (32451)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Particular average warranties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32451&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the subject-matter insured is warranted free from`
  line `particular average, the assured cannot recover for a loss of part, other than a loss incurred by a general`
  line `average sacrifice, unless the contract contained in the policy be apportionable; but, if the contract be`
  line `apportionable, the assured may recover for a total loss of any apportionable part.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the subject-matter insured is warranted free from particular average, either wholly or under`
  line `a certain percentage, the insurer is nevertheless liable for salvage charges, and for particular charges and`
  line `other expenses properly incurred pursuant to the provisions of the suing and labouring clause in order to`
  line `avert a loss insured against.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the policy otherwise provides, where the subject-matter insured is warranted free from`
  line `particular average under a specified percentage, a general average loss cannot be added to a particular`
  line `average loss to make up the specified percentage.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of ascertaining whether the specified percentage has been reached, regard shall be`
  line `had only to the actual loss suffered by the subject-matter insured. Particular charges and the expenses of`
  line `and incidental to ascertaining and proving the loss must be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (32452)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Successive losses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32452&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless the policy otherwise provides, and subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the insurer is liable for successive losses, even though the total amount of such losses may exceed the`
  line `sum insured.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, under the same policy, a partial loss, which has not been repaired or otherwise made good,`
  line `is followed by a total loss, the assured can only recover in respect of the total loss:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect the liability of the insurer under the suing and`
  line `labouring clause.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (32453)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Suing and labouring clause.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32453&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the policy contains a suing and labouring clause, the`
  line `engagement thereby entered into is deemed to be supplementary to the contract of insurance, and the`
  line `assured may recover from the insurer any expenses properly incurred pursuant to the clause, notwithstanding that the insurer may have paid for a total loss, or that the subject-matter may have been`
  line `warranted free from particular average, either wholly or under a certain percentage.`
  line
  line `(2) General average losses and contributions and salvage charges, as defined by this Act, are not`
  line `recoverable under the suing and labouring clause.`
  line
  line `(3) Expenses incurred for the purpose of averting or diminishing any loss not covered by the policy`
  line `are not recoverable under the suing and labouring clause.`
  line
  line `(4) It is the duty of the assured and his agents, in all cases, to take such measures as may be`
  line `reasonable for the purpose of averting or minimising a loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (32454)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Right of subrogation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32454&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the insurer pays for a total loss, either of the whole, or in the`
  line `case of goods of any apportionable part, of the subject-matter insured, he thereupon becomes entitled to`
  line `take over the interest of the assured in whatever may remain of the subject-matter so paid for, and he is`
  line `thereby subrogated to all the rights and remedies of the assured in and in respect of that subject-matter as`
  line `from the time of the casualty causing the loss.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the foregoing provisions, where the insurer pays for a partial loss, he acquires no title to`
  line `the subject-matter insured, or such part of it as may remain, but he is thereupon subrogated to all rights`
  line `and remedies of the assured in and in respect of the subject-matter insured as from the time of the casualty`
  line `causing the loss, in so far as the assured has been indemnified, according to this Act, by such payment for`
  line `the loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (32455)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Right of contribution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32455&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the assured is over-insured by double insurance, each insurer`
  line `is bound, as between himself and the other insurers, to contribute rateably to the loss in proportion to the`
  line `amount for which he is liable under his contract.`
  line
  line `(2) If any insurer pays more than his proportion of the loss, he is entitled to maintain a suit for`
  line `contribution against the other insurers, and is entitled to the like remedies as a surety who has paid more`
  line `than his proportion of the debt.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (32456)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Effect of under-insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32456&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Where the assured is insured for an amount less than the insurable`
  line `value, or, in the case of a valued policy, for an amount less than the policy valuation, he is deemed to be`
  line `his own insurer in respect of the uninsured balance.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (32457)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Enforcement of return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32457&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Where the premium, or a proportionate part thereof, is, by this Act,`
  line `declared to be returnable--`
  line
  line `(a) if already paid, it may be recovered by the assured from the insurer, and,`
  line
  line `(b) if unpaid, it may be retained by the assured or his agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (32458)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Return by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32458&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `Where the policy contains a stipulation for the return of the premium, or`
  line `a proportionate part thereof, on the happening of a certain event, and that event happens, the premium, or,`
  line `as the case may be, the proportionate part thereof, is thereupon returnable to the assured.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (32459)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Return for failure of consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32459&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the consideration for the payment of the`
  line `premium totally fails, and there has been no fraud or illegality on the part of the assured or his agents, the`
  line `premium is thereupon returnable to the assured.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the consideration for the payment of the premium is apportionable and there is a total`
  line `failure of any apportionable part of the consideration, a proportionate part of the premium is, under the`
  line `like conditions, thereupon returnable to the assured.`
  line
  line `(3) In particular:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the policy is void, or is avoided by the insurer as from the commencement of the risk,`
  line `the premium is returnable, provided there has been no fraud or illegality on the part of the assured;`
  line `but if the risk is not apportionable, and has once attached, the premium is not returnable;`
  line
  line `(b) where the subject-matter insured, or part thereof, has never been inperilled the premium, or, as`
  line `the case may be, a proportionate part thereof, is returnable:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the subject-matter has been insured "lost or not lost", and has arrived in`
  line `safety at the time when the contract is concluded, the premium is not returnable unless, at such time,`
  line `the insurer knew of the safe arrival;`
  line
  line `(c) where the assured has no insurable interest throughout the currency of the risk the premium is`
  line `returnable, provided that the rule does not apply to a policy effected by way of wagering;`
  line
  line `(d) where the assured has a defeasible interest which is terminated during the currency of the risk,`
  line `the premium is not returnable;`
  line
  line `(e) where the assured has over-insured under an unvalued policy, a proportionate part of the`
  line `premium is returnable;`
  line
  line `(f) subject to the foregoing provisions, where the assured has over-insured by double insurance, a`
  line `proportionate part of the several premiums is returnable:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the policies are effected at different times, and any earlier policy has at any time`
  line `borne the entire risk, or if a claim has been paid on the policy in respect of the full sum insured`
  line `thereby, no premium is returnable in respect of that policy, and when the double insurance is effected`
  line `knowingly by the assured no premium is returnable.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (32460)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Ratification by assured.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32460&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Where a contract of marine insurance is in good faith effected by one`
  line `person on behalf of another, the person on whose behalf it is effected may ratify the contract even after he`
  line `is aware of a loss.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (32461)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Implied obligation varied by agreement or usage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32461&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any right, duty, or liability`
  line `would arise under a contract of marine insurance by implication of law, it may be negatived or varied by`
  line `express agreement, or by usage, if the usage be such as to bind both parties to the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this section extend to any right, duty, or liability declared by this Act which`
  line `may be lawfully modified by agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (32462)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Reasonable time, etc., a question of fact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32462&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `Where by this Act any reference is made to`
  line `reasonable time, reasonable premium, or reasonable diligence, the question what is reasonable is a`
  line `question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (32463)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Covering note as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32463&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `Where there is a duly stamped policy, reference may be made, as`
  line `heretofore, to the slip or covering note, in any legal proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (32464)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to apply Act with modifications, etc., in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32464&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the provisions of this Act shall, in their application to`
  line `contracts of marine insurance relating to any class of ships exclusively used in inland navigation, be`
  line `subject to such conditions, exceptions and modifications as it may specify in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (32465)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Certain provisions to override Transfer of Property Act, 1882.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32465&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in clause (e)`
  line `of section 6 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), shall affect the provisions of`
  line `sections 17, 52, 53 and 79.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (32466)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286&sectionId=32466&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00006_196311_1517807318286
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The rules of law, including the law merchant, which applied to contracts of marine`
  line `insurance immediately before the commencement of this Act, save in so far as they are inconsistent with`
  line `the express provisions of this Act, shall continue to apply to contracts of marine insurance.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
